That's correct! When you apply Gaussian elimination to the 3 variable system you provided, you should end up with the following row echelon form:

\begin{align*}
\begin{pmatrix}
1 & 2 & 1 & 0 \\
0 & 1 & -\frac{7}{5} & 0 \\
0 & 0 & -\frac{24}{5} & 1 
\end{pmatrix}
\end{align*}

At this point, we can see that the third row implies that $0 = -\frac{24}{5}$, which is a contradiction. Therefore, there is no solution for the given system.

